# Services

## Struktur
Services enthalten wiederverwendbare Business Logic, getrennt von Vue-Komponenten.

```
src/services/
├── analysis/           # Analyse-Algorithmen
│   ├── index.ts        # Qualitative Analyse (Soundness, Struktur)
│   └── metricsCalculator.ts  # Process Metrics
├── file/               # Datei-Operationen
│   ├── fileService.ts  # Import/Export Koordination
│   ├── pnmlParser.ts   # PNML lesen
│   ├── pnmlWriter.ts   # PNML schreiben
│   ├── jsonParser.ts   # JSON Import/Export
│   └── imageExporter.ts # SVG/PNG Export
├── simulation/         # Simulation
│   ├── SimulationEngine.ts  # Diskrete Ereignissimulation
│   └── XESExporter.ts       # XES Log Export
└── templates/          # Vorlagen
    └── petriNetTemplates.ts  # Beispiel-Netze
```

## Service-Pattern
```typescript
// Singleton-Export für einfache Services
export const fileService = {
  async importFile(file: File): Promise<ImportResult> { /* ... */ },
  async exportToFile(net: PetriNet, options: ExportOptions): Promise<void> { /* ... */ },
}

// Klasse für komplexe Services mit State
export class SimulationEngine {
  constructor(net: PetriNet, config: SimulationConfig) { /* ... */ }
  run(): SimulationResult { /* ... */ }
}
```

## File Service
```typescript
// Import
const result = await fileService.importFile(file)
if (result.success) {
  store.loadNet(result.net)
}

// Export
await fileService.exportToFile(net, {
  format: 'pnml',  // oder 'json'
  includeLayout: true,
  filename: 'mynet.pnml'
})
```

## Simulation Engine
```typescript
const engine = new SimulationEngine(net, {
  cases: 100,
  maxTime: 3600,
  timeModel: { type: 'exponential', mean: 10 }
})
const result = engine.run()
// result.statistics, result.eventLog, etc.
```

## Templates
```typescript
import { templates, getTemplatesByCategory } from '@/services/templates/petriNetTemplates'

// Alle Templates
templates.forEach(t => console.log(t.nameKey))

// Nach Kategorie
const basicTemplates = getTemplatesByCategory('basic')

// Template laden
const net = template.create()
store.loadNet(net)
```

## Fehlerbehandlung
- Services werfen Exceptions bei Fehlern
- Komponenten fangen diese und zeigen User-Feedback
- Import-Errors als `ImportResult.errors[]` zurückgeben
